.TH "pci_epc_mem_alloc_addr" 9 "pci_epc_mem_alloc_addr" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pci_epc_mem_alloc_addr \- allocate memory address from EPC addr space
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void __iomem *" pci_epc_mem_alloc_addr
.BI "(struct pci_epc *epc "  ","
.BI "phys_addr_t *phys_addr "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "epc" 12
the EPC device on which memory has to be allocated
.IP "phys_addr" 12
populate the allocated physical address here
.IP "size" 12
the size of the address space that has to be allocated
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Invoke to allocate memory address from the EPC address space. This
is usually done to map the remote RC address into the local system.
